channel.title: Is this a good trade?
channel.description:
Well here's one for all you vehicle/truck enthusiasts. [img]https://ton.twitter.com/i/ton/data/dm/492010978301992962/492010978314567680/ymBhedrw.jpg:small[/img] This is my 2004 Heritage edition f150. Babied, nothing wrong with it whatsoever. 120k miles. Triton 5.4L V8. Tranny and 4 wd function as should. Basically a great babied truck. As I am a younger newer driver, insurance is through the roof (because newer vehicles cost more to repair, if something were to happen) for newer trucks, and this is what I am driving. And here is what I found:
1995 F-150 Clean title in hand Extended cab 302 4x4 Professionally rebuilt 4R70W AUTOMATIC transmission (less than 1500 miles) 130k on body - roughly 60k on motor New exterior transmission cooler 8' bed 4" Rough country suspension lift Rough country dual steering stabilizer 3" PA body lift 35" BFG TA/KO (less than 1500 miles) Brand new RC 15" steel wheels 1.5" Rough Country wheel spacers Eagle Eye projector halo headlights 4- 9" Hella off road lights (mounted but not hooked up) Visor and cab lights (wired, but not hooked up) Tinted windows Radiator core support redone New middle two bed cross braces Entire body Rhino lined Two mirrors New interior carpet/ seat covers/ cheetah print headliner/LED some light Brand new parts not installed that go with truck: Full length Flowtech headers Bully aluminum side steps Pro Comp 2" front leveling kit
And here is pictures: [img]http://images.craigslist.org/00Y0Y_k9XfCSLgZwu_600x450.jpg[/img] [img]http://images.craigslist.org/00y0y_2jHyJsEUJil_600x450.jpg[/img] Is this a good trade? He is interested and wants to trade. Since it is older it would be less on insurance, and I have been looking for a nice lifted truck. But I need more input from you guys. Thanks!

Actually, you’d be surprised. My 5.4L gets anywhere from 16-22 MPG. It’s not as much as your cars but hey. I have four wheel drive :P[/quote]

My 98 gmc Suburban gets 18-20, its a 350 smallblock chevy its a tank I can take that thing anywhere four wheel drive with a locker damn I love this gmc and I have a 42 gallon tank it was a firetruck carried the crew around seats 9 and four more in the back I use it to go camping took it in a mud hole got stuck put it in four wheel drive and crawled right out
